<title>GERMANY: DAG union rejects Lufthansa call for wage freeze.</title>
<headline>DAG union rejects Lufthansa call for wage freeze.</headline>
<dateline>FRANKFURT 1996-09-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>German white collar worker union DAG on Wednesday rejected national airline Deutsche Lufthansa AG's call to freeze wages.</p>
<p>Lufthansa's threat that a wage freeze is necessary to offset otherwise unavoidable job cuts &quot;will weigh heavily on wages talks&quot; scheduled to begin on Monday, DAG head negotiator Michael Tarp said in a statement.</p>
<p>&quot;The DAG is not willing to participate in such bloodletting every few years,&quot; Tarp said, pointing out that the union already agreed to large compromises in 1992.</p>
<p>-- Frankfurt Newsroom, +49 69 756525</p>
